FiDi Burger King located in a fairly busy area.  fairly large BK with a lot of seating options. relatively clean. while this location is not new... but the interior is in good shape. there is a bathroom for customers in the back. and the drink dispensers are by the register.  the pluses is that this BK abides by national promotions (like the Halloween Whopper), pricing deals (1 cent Whopper deal), etc. you can use the BK app to mobile order here whereas other BKs aren't on the mobile app system.  the minuses: when it's crowded it's crowded. service after ordering is slow (kitchen seems to be over-capacity during busy times). and the mobile app orders are just called out (there's no digital display showing orders in progress or ready like McD's).  food is standard for a a Burger King: fast (most times) and cheap.  the staff work hard from what i can tell. however if the lines are long here, bypass and go someplace else.  drops mic cuz i don't tell whoppers
